  "title": "IC Design Engineer (Digital IC Design/Analog /Mixed-Signal)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Collaborate with Senior Engineers for design requirements and specifications.</li>\n  <li>Assist in <strong>Analog</strong>, <strong>mixed-signal</strong>, and <strong>digital IC design</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Participate in RTL coding and verification for digital ICs.</li>\n  <li>Support design verification tasks.</li>\n  <li>Conduct circuit simulations and analysis using <strong>Cadence, Synopsys, and Mentor Graphics tools</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Assist layout engineers with floor planning.</li>\n  <li>Analyze and debug silicon failures, suggesting design improvements.</li>\n  <li>Contribute to the development of design methodologies to enhance efficiency.</li>\n  <li>Document design work and test plans.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure successful tape-out.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s Degree in Electrical Engineering or equivalents.</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of relevant working experience.</li>\n  <li>Understanding the <strong>IC development flow</strong> in advanced CMOS processes, including <strong>design, layout, and tape-out.</strong></li>\n  <li>Understanding the fundamental theories of digital or analog circuit design.</li>\n  <li>Capability to generate inventive designs and circuit solutions tailored to fulfill customer needs.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>__________________________________________________________</strong></p>\n<p><strong>HOW TO APPLY :</strong></p>\n<p>Interested candidates, please submit your resume by clicking on <strong>“Quick Apply” </strong>or contact <strong>win@hkmsvs.com</strong> for more details.</p>\n<p><strong>Please provide following information in the resume for immediate processing</strong></p>\n<p>1) Reasons for leaving current and/or last employment</p>\n<p>2) Last drawn and/or current salary</p>\n<p>3) Expected salary</p>\n<p>4) Date of availability and/or Notice Period</p>\n<p><strong>All applications will be treated in strictest confidence and only shortlisted candidates will be notified</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Wee Wai Dan</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA License No : 03C5391</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA Reg No : R22109628</strong></p>",
